---
// Educational section about call handling problems
---

<section class="call-handling-pain bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-50 to-gray-100 py-16">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4">

    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
        Every Missed Call = Lost Revenue
      </h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        Industry research shows contractors miss 30-60% of customer calls.
        <span class="text-[#FF6B35] font-semibold">Those customers call your competitor next.</span>
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- The Problem Grid -->
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-12">

      <!-- Problem 1: Owner Answers -->
      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md border-l-4 border-red-500">
        <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-red-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mr-4">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-red-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M16 7a4 4 0 11-8 0 4 4 0 018 0zM12 14a7 7 0 00-7 7h14a7 7 0 00-7-7z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900">You Answer</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          When the owner answers calls, they're often:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-red-500 mr-2">✗</span>
            <span>On a ladder installing equipment</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-red-500 mr-2">✗</span>
            <span>Driving between job sites</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-red-500 mr-2">✗</span>
            <span>Talking with another customer</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-red-500 mr-2">✗</span>
            <span>At the parts store or bank</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <div class="mt-4 p-3 bg-red-50 rounded">
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-600">Missed Call Rate:</div>
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-600">60-80%</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Problem 2: Spouse/Family -->
      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md border-l-4 border-orange-500">
        <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-orange-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mr-4">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-orange-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 3a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0zM7 10a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900">Spouse/Family</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          Family members helping out face challenges:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-orange-500 mr-2">✗</span>
            <span>Can't answer technical questions</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-orange-500 mr-2">✗</span>
            <span>Juggling kids, errands, other jobs</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-orange-500 mr-2">✗</span>
            <span>Customers want "the owner"</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-orange-500 mr-2">✗</span>
            <span>Inconsistent availability</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <div class="mt-4 p-3 bg-orange-50 rounded">
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-600">Missed Call Rate:</div>
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-orange-600">40-60%</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Problem 3: Answering Service -->
      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md border-l-4 border-yellow-500">
        <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-yellow-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mr-4">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-yellow-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M3 5a2 2 0 012-2h3.28a1 1 0 01.948.684l1.498 4.493a1 1 0 01-.502 1.21l-2.257 1.13a11.042 11.042 0 005.516 5.516l1.13-2.257a1 1 0 011.21-.502l4.493 1.498a1 1 0 01.684.949V19a2 2 0 01-2 2h-1C9.716 21 3 14.284 3 6V5z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900">Answering Service</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          Traditional answering services struggle with:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-yellow-500 mr-2">✗</span>
            <span>Sound impersonal and generic</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-yellow-500 mr-2">✗</span>
            <span>Can't book appointments immediately</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-yellow-500 mr-2">✗</span>
            <span>Customers hang up without leaving info</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-yellow-500 mr-2">✗</span>
            <span>Messages get delayed or lost</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <div class="mt-4 p-3 bg-yellow-50 rounded">
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-600">Missed Call Rate:</div>
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-yellow-600">20-40%</div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- The Real Cost -->
    <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg border-2 border-[#FF6B35] mb-12">
      <div class="text-center mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Here's What Actually Happens</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600">When a customer can't reach you on the first call...</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 text-center">
        <div class="p-4">
          <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-[#FF6B35] mb-2">78%</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Call your competitor next</div>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4">
          <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-[#FF6B35] mb-2">62%</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Won't leave a voicemail</div>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4">
          <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-[#FF6B35] mb-2">41%</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Never call back if you miss them twice</div>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4">
          <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-[#FF6B35] mb-2">$0</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Revenue from that lead</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- The Solution Teaser -->
    <div class="text-center">
      <div class="inline-block bg-gradient-to-r from-[#FF6B35] to-[#E55A25] text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-full mb-4">
        <span class="font-bold">✓ There's a Better Way</span>
      </div>
      <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
        What if every call was answered in 2 rings?
      </h3>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        AI-powered reception that sounds human, knows your business, books appointments,
        and <span class="font-bold text-[#FF6B35]">never misses a call</span> — even at 2am.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .call-handling-pain {
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .call-handling-pain::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: -50%;
    left: -50%;
    width: 200%;
    height: 200%;
    background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(255, 107, 53, 0.05) 0%, transparent 70%);
    animation: pulse 15s infinite;
  }

  @keyframes pulse {
    0%, 100% { transform: scale(1) rotate(0deg); }
    50% { transform: scale(1.1) rotate(180deg); }
  }
</style>
